==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Splurge
<hw>Splurge</hw> <pr>(spl⟦ucir⟧rj)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A blustering
demonstration, or great effort; a great display.</def> <mark>[Slang,
U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splurge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Splurge
<hw>Splurge</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a great display in any
way, especially in oratory.</def> <mark>[Slang, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. To spend money freely or extravagantly, in one episode; usu.
with "on" -- as, to <ex>splurge</ex> on a new hi-fi system. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- v.t. to spend extravagantly. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splutter</ent>⟦br⟧
